<h1>Kenn Wilson</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://www.kennwilson.com/now">kennwilson.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Portland
OR
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Co-founder of Colette Media, publisher of Colette Patterns and Seamwork Magazine.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
We publish beautiful and classic sewing patterns, tools, and resources to help revive the art of sewing.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I enjoy helping people by enabling their creativity. I’ve also became disillusioned with working for others and came to realize that the way to really gain control over your life is to work for yourself.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You don't need to fear growth. With a good team and support you can overcome most any bumps you encounter along the way. Interpret “growth” here whichever way you prefer.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Dune, by Frank Herbert (1965). Everyone should read this.
</p>

